@startuml scenario_start_stop_signal_flow
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor #FFFFFF
skinparam defaultFontName Arial
skinparam defaultFontSize 11
skinparam sequenceMessageAlign center
skinparam responseMessageBelowArrow true

title Scenario Start / Stop Signal Flow\n(Input_Console -> TEST_SCN -> scenario state / lamps)

actor "Operator\n(Input Console)" as Operator #F4F7FB
participant "Input_Console\nScenario tab" as Panel #E8F0FE
participant "TEST_SCN\nscenario owner" as SCN #FFE6E6
participant "Scenario state\nreadback seams" as State #E8F7E8
participant "Execution lamps\nSTOP / WARN / RUN" as Lamps #FFF4CC

== Start Request ==

Operator -> Panel : Click SCN preset
Panel -> SCN : Test::scenarioCommand
SCN -> SCN : applyScenarioPanelRequest(scenarioId, 0)
SCN -> SCN : beginScenarioExecution()
SCN -> SCN : applyScenarioPreset()
SCN -> State : Test::testScenario = scenarioId
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioCommandAck = scenarioId
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioActiveId = scenarioId
SCN -> Lamps : scenarioLampStop = 0\nscenarioLampWarn = 0\nscenarioLampRun = 1
SCN -> SCN : scheduleScenarioEvaluation()

== Evaluation / Result ==

SCN -> State : Test::scenarioSettledId = active scenario
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioEvaluatedId = active scenario
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioResult = 0 or 1
SCN -> Lamps : refresh STOP / WARN / RUN lamps
note right of SCN
Lamp rule:
- activeScenarioId != 0 -> RUN
- ack != 0 and evaluated != 0 and result == 0 -> WARN
- otherwise STOP
end note

== Stop / Manual ==

Operator -> Panel : Click STOP / MANUAL
Panel -> SCN : Test::scenarioStopReq
SCN -> SCN : applyScenarioPanelRequest(0, 1)
SCN -> SCN : stopScenarioExecution()
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioCommandAck = 0
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioActiveId = 0
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioSettledId = 0
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioEvaluatedId = 0
SCN -> State : Test::scenarioResult = 0
SCN -> State : Test::testScenario = 0
SCN -> Lamps : scenarioLampStop = 1\nscenarioLampWarn = 0\nscenarioLampRun = 0

Operator <- State : Current / Ack / Result boxes update
Operator <- Lamps : execution status LEDs update

note over Operator, Lamps
Representative runtime chain
1. Scenario tab writes Test::scenarioCommand or Test::scenarioStopReq
2. TEST_SCN accepts, mirrors, and locks the active scenario
3. TEST_SCN publishes commandAck / activeId / evaluatedId / result
4. TEST_SCN also drives STOP / WARN / RUN lamp seams
5. Input_Console reads back the same seams as the scenario state panel
end note

@enduml
